review_blob: Low head, a lot of sediment.  Pleasant malt aroma, but taste lacks complexity.  Easy drinking, but not exciting at all
Very thick.  Incredibly rich flavors that constantly change.  Strong chocolate flavor, oats, and even a subtle fruity taste.  Good malt flavors.
One of the smoothest beers I have ever had.  Sweet aroma, a slightly thin head, fruity, hoppy taste
A sparkling beer, with a sweet apple taste.  Strong yeast flavors start off pleasant, but can leave a subtle but mildly acrid aftertaste

review_blob: Is a bit fruity, with a slightly nutty taste.  Highly carbonated.  Very good complement to a meal, but not interesting enough on its own
